# Purpose

Enforce Express module structure, request context usage, middleware wiring, transaction patterns, SSE, and response shapes. Coding conventions (naming, imports, error handling, logging) are in `backend/coding-standards.mdc`.

# Rules

## Module Structure

Every feature module (`auth`, `jobs`) MUST follow this layout:

```
modules/<name>/
├── <name>-controller.ts   Route handlers — read from req, call db/services, respond
├── <name>-middleware.ts   Request validation and guards (call next() or throw)
├── <name>-routing.ts      Express Router — wire middleware chain to controller
├── <name>-registry.ts     OpenAPI path registration (zod-to-openapi)
├── schemas/               Zod schemas for request/response shapes
└── types/                 TypeScript types derived from schemas
```

## Controllers

- Async functions with signature `(req: Request<Params, ResBody, ReqBody>, res: Response)`.
- Read inputs from `req.body`, `req.params`, `req.query`, `req.context`.
- Call `res.status(HttpStatusCode.X).json({ success: true, data: ... })` on success.
- Use `HttpStatusCode` enum from `shared/enums/http-status-codes`.
- DO NOT put business logic or validation in controllers — delegate to middleware and services.
- Re-throw all caught errors after cleanup (transaction abort, session end).

## Request Context (`req.context`)

All cross-cutting resources are accessed via `req.context`:

| Property | Description |
|---|---|
| `req.context.db.repository.users` | User DB operations (`UserRepository`) |
| `req.context.db.repository.jobs` | Jobs DB operations (`JobsRepository`) |
| `req.context.db.transaction` | MongoDB transaction session source |
| `req.context.user.id` | Authenticated user ID (string) |
| `req.context.scheduler` | Cron job scheduling |
| `req.context.delegator` | Job execution delegation |
| `req.context.emitter` | SSE event bus |

## Middleware

- Middleware functions MUST call `next()` on success or `throw` a typed exception on failure.
- Input validation middleware uses `validateRequestPayload(schema, req.body, ErrorMessage.X)`.
- Auth guard: `authenticateContextMiddleware` (sets `req.context.user`).
- Resource injection: `contextResourceMiddleware` (attaches db, scheduler, delegator, emitter).

## Routing

- Routes MUST use constants from `shared/constants/routes`. DO NOT hardcode route strings.
- Middleware chain order: rate limiter → `validateUserInput` → domain middleware → controller.

## Transactions

When an operation must be atomic across multiple writes:

```typescript
const session = req.context.db.transaction.startSession();
let isCommitted = false;
try {
    session.startTransaction();
    // ... DB operations with session passed in ...
    await session.commitTransaction();
    isCommitted = true;
    // ... post-commit side effects (schedule, delegate) ...
} catch (error) {
    if (!isCommitted) await session.abortTransaction();
    logger.error('Operation failed', { error: error as Error });
    throw error;
} finally {
    await session.endSession();
}
```

## SSE (Server-Sent Events)

- Set `Content-Type: text/event-stream`, `Cache-Control: no-cache`, `Connection: keep-alive`, then `res.flushHeaders()`.
- Use `sendSSE(res, payload)` from `aop/http/sse`.
- Remove all event listeners on `req.on('close', ...)`.

## Response Shape

```typescript
// Success — single resource
{ success: true, data: <payload> }

// Success — with auth metadata
{ success: true, data: <payload>, meta: { timestamp: number } }

// Success — paginated list
{ success: true, data: [], limit: number, offset: number, count: number }

// Error (produced by exceptionsMiddleware, never by controllers directly)
{ success: false, issues: ZodIssue[], code: string, timestamp: string }
```

# Required Commands

```bash
cd backend
npm start                 # ts-node-dev dev server (port 1000)
npm run lint              # ESLint
npm run lint-fix          # ESLint auto-fix
npm run type-check        # tsc --noEmit
```

# Anti-Patterns

- DO NOT call `res.json()` for error responses — throw typed exceptions.
- DO NOT access MongoDB directly in controllers — use `req.context.db.repository.*`.
- DO NOT schedule cron jobs before `commitTransaction()`.
- DO NOT forget `session.endSession()` in `finally`.
- DO NOT hardcode route strings in routing files.
